0 Fund issues -- tConcluding remarks -- tInfrastructure, political economy and Africa’s transformational agenda -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aGood infrastructure is essential for socio-economic growth and sustainable development. Safe and accessible water supplies, reliable energy, good transport networks and communications technology are all vital to a region’s development agenda. This book presents a comprehensive exploration of the state of infrastructure in Africa and provides an integrated analysis of the challenges the sector faces, based on extensive fieldwork across the continent. Contributors with a wide range of expertise challenge current policy, practice and thinking on issues including the politics of infrastructure development, social inclusion, domestic resource mobilisation and infrastructure financing. The book will be an important resource for academic researchers, students and early career development professionals as well as policymakers and NGOs engaged in dialoguing the infrastructure development options for Africa.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aEconomic developmentzAfrica. 0aInfrastructure (Economics)zAfrica. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / City Planning & Urban Development.2bisacsh1 aAdam, Abdoulaye, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAdam, Lishan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnyanwu, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrixiova, Zuzana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChaponda, Taz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChetty, Mayuree, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChinganya, O